Smith Barney, Harris Upham and Coanalyst James Wilbur removed Hercules Inc from the firm'srecommended list, citing the firm's moves into the aerospacebusiness, traders said.    Hercules fell 2-1/4 to 59-1/4 on 595,000 shares. Wilbur wasnot immediately available for comment.    Sources said Wilbur believes Hercules will be successful inits diversification, but he told clients the stock market ismore receptive now to chemical companies than aerospacecompanies. Reuter&#3;